It really is pathetic what the epics have done to EQ. People get so exited and so frustrated and so bitter.<br>
<br>
Verant dropped the ball on Epics, almost as seriously as they dropped the ball on post level 50 expansion.<br>
<br>
To all the Non Tunare Paladins without Epics who are bitter and petty about Tunarian Paladins with ND: I feel sorry for you. Being so greedy, petty and self centered is a sad way to live life or play a game.<br>
<br>
ND was put in by Verant just as was every other quest in game that EVERYONE has EVER done or taken advantage of. Begrudging one class or another for an item you cannot use is selfish. NO MATTER WHAT.<br>
<br>
I have Nature's Defender. I have no other weapons because I have ND. I have passed on dragon books because I have ND. I KNOW at 1 Paladin got his FD because I passed on books. I KNOW 3 more will get the FD because I am passing on books.<br>
<br>
If you did not get an easy sword I am sorry. Blame Verant. They make the quests. Don't balme the people who get LUCKY by being able to take advantage of the quest.<br>
<br>
If all you ever see is the negative or me, me, me then the game is gonna be pretty crappy for you no matterif you have ONE nice item (FD) or not.<br>
<br>
In the end the FD is just a weapon, despite the quest, or the potential for pesronal accomplishment on doing the quest.<br>
<br>
It is a fact that any quest item past level 45 is not a personal accomplishment, but an act of support from your friends and guildmates. If you have friends and guildmates in EQ that give a rat's ass about your and a tiny bit of luck on drops (and maybe too much online time), you can and will get any item in game.<br>
<br>
But never begrudge someone else simply because they got LUCKY. The ND quest was a stroke of nothing but LUCK for Tunare paladins in game. Why be pissed about it.<br>
<br>
May as well be pissed that someone beat you on a roll for a FS sword when you were level 14.<br>
<br>
If the Epic weapons are continued in Luclin so be it. I am not worried. Frankly I do not think they will be as I try to stay pretty informed and have never seen a post by Verant saying such. And ALL the posts say ing otherwise have been 'I talked to a GM' or 'My firends talked to a GM' or some such hearsay.<br>
<br>
But if they are I will do them like i do the FD quest. If I get comonents, great. If not great. I am not gonna worry about what is basically an issue decided by pure luck (whether the cold book drops of Gore or not).<br>
<br>
Folks get some maturity and perspective. <p><center>
