<br>
Why would paladins need to kill good things in the Plane of Health?  Tunarean paladins don't currently need to kill good things in the Plane of Growth, so I don't understand where you get the idea that Nife paladins would need to do so in the Plane of Health.<br>
Quests can send players pretty much anywhere.  The key part for a Plane of Underfoot or a Plane of Health quest that consolidated it as a quest for the appropriate plane would be that the person issueing the quest was based there.  If I go to the Plane of Underfoot (when it comes in, of course), and am issued a quest to kill the 'parts' of Veeshan found in PoA, there is nothing to prevent me from taking the drops from those kills and coming back to Underfoot to collect a reward.<br>
Or, just as in the ND quest, a paladin of Nife or Brell might be asked to remove corrupted denizens of the plane who are now posing a hazard to the regular inhabitants.<br>
Thus far, the evils have had to kill the inhabitants of their deities' planes, but the sole 'good' plane that has gone in so far has discouraged that.<br>
